Shortly thereafter, Canada and Ireland are invaded as unrestricted submarine warfare guts the economy of the U.K. France surrenders to Germany/Austria, Canada is carved into American states (1928, 29-32), and Ireland becomes an American Protectorate. America vows to return to isolationism after the war; Britain vows its Empire will survive. The badly beaten French vow revenge for this loss; in 1929, a French Nationalist (and WWI survivor) named DeGaulle rises to power in a far right party, vowing to rearm, resist, and push the Kaiser into the Baltic. Several far right parties coalesce around DeGaulle, and his speeches become things of spectacle. When civil war breaks out in Spain, he sends more than fifty thousand French Soldiers to eliminate the 'dangerous' socialist Republic. France declares itself "Nationaliste" Spain, by 1930, is an ally, under General Francisco Franco. Italy joins into this alliance in 1932. The U.K. flirts with joining, but does not. Meanwhile, the Germans are being bled dry by the 'Great Northern War' which pitted the German Empire and Finland against the Soviet Union in a defensive war against the Soviets expanding into the Baltic states and Finland. With their economies weakened, the Austrians collapse (in 1934) leading to several years of disarray before another government can be seated.The Monarchy is gone, however. In 1935, mass protests and riots cripple Germany itself, and Frederick III is assassinated in Leipzig, ostensibly by French provacateurs.  America, meanwhile, fights a dirty war against Mexican Guerrillas, armed and trained by the fleeing Confederates and Anglo-French mercenaries. Whole villages are quietly eliminated, and thousands of soldiers die in the relentless, tireless war of attrition. As President Teddy Roosevelt laments 'There are no good wars; only good men doing terrible things." (L.A. Times, 1932)  In the Far East, Japan expands into China, Taiwan, Mongolia, and, on April 14th, 1934,  crosses the Amur River, into Siberia, with a sudden, unprovoked attack on Port Arthur that destroys the Soviet Eastern Fleet completely. This is done to get at Soviet fuel supplies, needed by the Japanese in order to expand further in China. By the end of May, 1934, more than a million Imperial Japanese Soldiers are in Siberia, and Stalin is forced to attempt making a temporary peace with the Germans to move his beleaguered forces east.  July 3rd, 1934. Stalin is killed in the Kremlin as the Germans firebomb Moscow with long range Focke-Wulf 202 Condor Bombers. *** WW2***

text: This movie looks AWESOME!!! Although it's kind of sad that a movie is doing a FPS better than most games these days.  Probably one of the few possible flaws in this movie is if the main bad guys (which I'm presuming to be the guy with the buzzcut who knocks you off the bridge and holds your "wife" at gunpoint and the long-haired blonde dude, Hate them already so good job trailer) get lame quick deaths like a last minute decapitation or headshot.   I bring this up because in most stories, the villain IS the conflict and driving force of the story and thus they deserve a memorable sendoff (and an agonizing one in the case of despicable villains), but time and TIME again writers and directors just go for cliched, anticlimactic, and BORING deaths like headshots (I especially HATE it when the villain wails on the hero for a good 5 minutes and the hero retaliates with only one or two fatal hits. LAME!!!).  Here's me hoping and PRAYING the main villains in this badass-looking movie get brutal, painful (and most importantly, memorable) deaths.

text: This will suffer the same problems on why I think the FPS camera is stupid in FPS games but even amplified because this is a movie. First of all, the motion sickness, seriously, this is one of the reasons why people hate shaky cam and not it will happen for practically the whole movie since this is an action film. Second, this is the fact that I find particularly stupid, since your in a first person, you can't see your character's emotions and their hand will constantly be visible, they have to do EVERYTHING within eyesight and I found that stupid in FPS games and I find that doubly stupid in a movie. Seriously, I just cringe whenever I see the characters hands awkwardly flail around his face. And frankly, as a movie, this just feels pretentious. Like they just want to stand out from other generic action flicks so they just decided to appeal to gamers and film it in a 1st person perspective. Hopefully if they can pull this off properly that this would just be an interesting experiment rather than becoming a trend.

text: I have been waiting for this for so long. Ever since I saw the very first Biting elbows video, I was like "There needs to be a movie like this, shut up and take my fucking money"  After waiting with bated breath for what seems like an eternity, this movie is finally coming out to theaters. I'm excited to see the way the writers and directors decided to tell the story, since it's all in semi-real time, and the story is going to have to be told in context to the main character and also act as expository dialogue and storytelling, which would be a challenge to say the least, not even counting the first person perspective of the movie - with that added variable, I think this movie is going to be very good. Sure it's going to be a popcorn action packed thrill ride, probably lacking in traditional storytelling - but I think that the people behind this movie will more than make up for the nontraditional approach by skillfully panning to the film's demographic.   regardless if this movie is a one off flash in the pan, or the first of many badass movies from this studio, I think it's going to be successful, if not a blockbuster, this movie has the ability to become a cult classic.  Hell. It's almost already my favorite movie and It's not even out yet.

text: I'll admit, I'm here because of Payday 2, but then again, that's how I found out about John Wick as well, and I love that movie.    I'll be honest, The draw to this movie is mostly the style. This is obviously an attempt at making a movie in the style of an FPS, right down to the silent protagonist, Now I'll admit, in terms of games, I'm not really a fan of silent characters, but there's at least a reason for it in this,  but I digress. The plot seems a little cliche, but that's just first impression, it could be a lot deeper than we know. The action looks awesome, and Sharlto Copley looks to be having a lot of fun with this, and I really want to know about the world that's been created.  Bottom line. You have my attention, and probably price of admission.

author: Alex Vish

text: Hardcore Henry (2016) is INSANELY awesome!!!  If I could rate it a 20, I would, just from the shear story telling, character investment and novel first-person POV, not to mention all the video game tropes, puns, and long shots!!  At least 90% of the movie are long shots, that's how well it was directed!  It contains a LOT of elements from Counter Strike, Modern Warfare, Half- Life 2, Portal and Mirrors Edge, so if you like those games, you should absolutely love this movie!  It has a LOT of gore in it, so I wouldn't recommend it to the squeamish, but if you're a high-octane trueblooded alpha male like myself, you should absolutely love it!  There were scenes I really loved and it was all done EXTREMELY artistically!! and I do say, in mostly good tastes!  There is TONS of gore, I got overwhelmed in the last 15 minutes, and there is a LOT of [amazing] frontal nudity. Overall, it was an AMAZING film!  My predictions were correct, I seriously think this started a completely new genre, one major push forward toward immersive First Person Point of View 3D virtual reality movies.

The actions scenes were cool but it gets repetitive constantly seeing action throughout the entire fucking movie and barely any hint of exposition that properly explains what the actual fuck is going on.  No real characters, the comedy was bland and it was just bad. This movie had so much potential, and although it was groundbreaking and led to the possibilities of more movies like this, it just did not deliver in atmosphere and story despite the design of the movie and film production.

There is alot of dark comedy. The movie borders into the gore and I don't know if action guys will be OK with it.  The 3rd act gets very violent.   This is a spoiler for one way that Henry kills a guy. ....              *SPOILER*   - Henry is part machine. He pulls his own eye out and there are wires and veins and legiments attached to the eye.   Henry wraps the chord of his eye around the guy's face and wraps it so tight that the guy's face cuts off. The whole movie is shot in first person.   I give this movie 4 out of 5 vodkas

text: I used to like violent films but after the shooting at a junior school in America and the recent terrorist attacks I find over the top ones like this and Shoot Em Up in bad taste.  Putting this level of violence to a happy song by Queen doesn't sit well with me.  I don't fully subscribe to violence in real life being related to what watch but I think we have to be careful making killing seem a laugh like this trailer does.  Violent films of the past weren't making the killings seem like nothing the way this does and say Crank does.  There were exceptions, of course, like Commando but they were came across as more grown-up.  I'll watch this but I'm sure it will suck and won't be as well made as MARKED for Death.

text: Just saw this! It's a decent movie. The first-person-perspective was really interesting, and surprisingly not hard to watch! The effects were great, and the action was awesome. The stuntwork was downright phenomenal! The acting was okay, and the story was pretty interesting, but crazy. It left a lot of questions unanswered! But in the end, it was a really fun movie to watch. It doesn't try to be serious, and that's part of what makes this movie so fun. If you're in the mood for shoot 'em up action and not much else, 'Hardcore Henry' is the way to go! It really is hardcore!   Overall rating: 7.5/10!
author: Comedy Bros

text: Fuckin' AMAZING movie!! Not the most "intellectual" plot, but c'mon, it's a "guilty pleasure" action flick. It doesn't pretend to be something it's not, and what it's trying to be, it does insanely perfectly. Some of the best fight scenes and stunts I've ever seen in my entire life. I'd put this in a close 2nd place behind Mad Max: Fury Road as one of the greatest action movies ever made. No, it's not as "pretty" as Fury Road, but the action will have you on the edge of your seat from beginning to end, with hardly any breathing room for anything else. If you haven't seen this, it needs to be the next movie you watch. My wife typically doesn't like action movies, and even she dug this one. It's THAT good. :D
